FBIS3-54172 "drnes015_o_94002" FBIS-NES-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 SYRIA Leaders, Citizens Mourn Death of Basil al-Asad 'Arafat Offers Condolences to al-Asad JN2301195994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1915 GMT 23 Jan 94 JN2301195994 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Yasir 'Arafat, head of the PLO Executive Committee, and the accompanying delegation left the Humaymim airport in Latakia this evening after offering their condolences to President al-Asad on the death of Staff Major Paratrooper Engineer Basil al-Asad, whose demise has been such a national loss. During his short visit, Yasir 'Arafat was accompanied by a delegation, including Faruq Qaddumi, head of the PLO Political Department; and Muhammad Ghunaym, Yasir 'Abd-Rabbuh, and Yasir 'Amr, members of the PLO Executive Committee; and Muhammad Jihad, member of Fatah Central Committee. 'Arafat and the accompanying delegation were seen off by Interior Minister Dr. Muhammad Harbah. 'Arafat and the accompanying delegation arrived in al-Qardahah today to offer their condolences to President Hafiz al-Asad on the death of Staff Major Paratrooper Basil Hafiz al-Asad.
